I think some of the reason people don&#39;t use the SwingUI in their main 
method is because of the desire to use dynamic loading - with a GUI 
there&#39;s the notion that the GUI testrunner will be running and will load 
new classes as/when they become available, so the GUI testrunner should 
run *its* main(), rather than the class that contains the tests.

Toby
P.S.
My biggest gripe is why aren&#39;t the test runners properly documented? 
Nothing in the API docs, nothing in the &quot;how to&quot; docs of any 
consequence. It surprises me that the main entry point of use is not 
well documented!

